# ApplySeatingPlanCommand

## Summary

Applies a complete seating arrangement to a Table Seating Planner card: it loads the planner with `GetCardCommand`, expands each party-head guest id into the full party (companions linked via `parentGuest`), and writes `seatedGuests` on every table — tables omitted from the plan are emptied. The plan is validated deterministically: out-of-range table indexes and unknown party ids are skipped and reported, per-table capacity is enforced (overflow is trimmed, and `section` grids are regrown to fit), and leftover parties are auto-seated by VIP status and category priority while honouring `reservedCategories`. Input is an `ApplySeatingPlanInput` card (`plannerCardId`, `assignments` of `TableAssignmentField`, optional `summary`); output is an `ApplySeatingPlanResult` (`seatedCount`, `message`). It makes no AI call itself — it is the deterministic half of the AI seating flow.

## Import

```js
import {
  ApplySeatingPlanCommand,
  TableAssignmentField,
} from '../commands/apply-seating-plan-command';
```

## Usage

In this package the command is not called from a component. It is registered on the Seat Arranger skill card (`Skill/seat-arranger.json`), and the AI assistant executes it after reasoning out the arrangement — the planner opens that room with `UseAiAssistantCommand` (see `components/tsp.gts`):

```json
{
  "codeRef": {
    "name": "ApplySeatingPlanCommand",
    "module": "../commands/apply-seating-plan-command"
  },
  "requiresApproval": false
}
```

Invoked directly, the input shape is:

```js
let ctx = this.args.context?.commandContext;
let result = await new ApplySeatingPlanCommand(ctx).execute({
  plannerCardId: planner.id,
  assignments: [
    new TableAssignmentField({ tableIndex: 0, partyIds: [avaId, noahId] }),
    new TableAssignmentField({ tableIndex: 1, partyIds: [miaId] }),
  ],
  summary: 'Family up front, friends by the dance floor.',
});
```
